<paragraph blockId="7.[151,347,909,936]" box="[151,347,909,936]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,347,909,936]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Hood" authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1908" box="[151,347,909,936]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Allothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,347,909,936]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,909,936]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">Allothrips</emphasis>
Hood
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,981,1187]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">
This genus currently includes 24, usually wingless, species living in leaf litter worldwide. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[1274,1436,981,1007]" firstAuthor="Mound" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" pagination="23 - 36" refId="ref6919" refString="Mound, L. A. (1972) Polytypic species of spore-feeding Thysanoptera in the genus Allothrips Hood (Phlaeothripidae). Australian Journal of Entomology, 11, 23 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1440 - 6055.1972. tb 01602. x" type="journal article" year="1972">Mound (1972)</bibRefCitation>
treated most of these as sub-species within two nominal species, the European 
<taxonomicName authority="Priesner" authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1925" box="[1066,1323,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Allothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pillichellus">
<emphasis box="[1066,1224,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">A. pillichellus</emphasis>
Priesner
</taxonomicName>
(with the basal half of the tube yellow) and the North American 
<taxonomicName authority="Hood" authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1908" box="[793,1056,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Allothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacephalus">
<emphasis box="[793,987,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">A. megacephalus</emphasis>
Hood
</taxonomicName>
(with the tube brown to reddish brown), these subspecies are now usually treated as full species (
<bibRefCitation accessDate="2019-05-01" author="ThripsWiki" box="[873,1071,1089,1115]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" publicationUrl="http://thrips.info/wiki/" refId="ref7542" refString="ThripsWiki (2019) providing information on the World's thrips. Available from: http: // thrips. info / wiki / (accessed 1 May 2019)" title="providing information on the World's thrips" type="url" year="2019">ThripsWiki 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Only 
<taxonomicName authority="Mound" authorityName="Mound" authorityYear="1972" box="[1152,1376,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Allothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bournieri">
<emphasis box="[1152,1288,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">A. bournieri</emphasis>
Mound
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,184,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[197,1390,179,1862]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Fungus feeding thrips species of Iran (1) Hindsiothrips sisakhti (female); (2) Idiothrips bellus (female); (3) Hoplandrothrips bidens (female); (4) Liophloeothrips arganicus (female); (5) Hoplothrips (female); (6) Cephalothrips monilicornis (female); (7) Cephalothrips coxalis (female); (8) Allothrips bournieri (female); (9) Stictothrips farsi sp. n. (female); (10) Stictothrips farsi sp. n. (male); (11) Pseudocryptothrips meridionalis (female); (12) Megathrips flavipes (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3364946/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) is reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[369,417,1125,1151]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">Iran</collectingCountry>
, based on both sexes collected from leaf litter in 
<collectingRegion box="[965,1118,1125,1151]" country="Iran" name="Fars" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">Fars province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei" box="[1133,1281,1125,1151]" firstAuthor="Minaei" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref6476" refString="Minaei, K. (2011) Fungal spore-feeding thrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae: Idolothripinae) from Iran with record of a fourth genus. Journal of Insect Science, 11, 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="2011">Minaei 2011</bibRefCitation>
). This species is otherwise known only from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[598,674,1161,1187]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">France</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[728,795,1161,1187]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">Spain</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
